  "doc_id": "15092",
  "text": "Human papilloma virus-positive HNSCC appears to be different from HPV-negative HNSCC in both molecular and clinical features [CITATION_1] . In general, it is recommended that at least two standardised and recognised methods should be used to confirm the diagnosis of clinically relevant HPV-positive HNSCC. This is underscored in this project as a clear separation in the PCA plots and heatmaps could only be achieved when at least two out of three positive criteria were met. Human papilloma virus status clearly has an influence on the miRNA expression profiles.",
